        <category>code_sanity</category>
        <conditions/>
        <description>Under some circumstances the platform auto-generates sys_wizard_answer records when (task-derived) tables are created.&#13;
Such auto-generated records are set to order "100".&#13;
In some cases these Wizard Answers may be useful, in other cases they may not. Either way, developers should make a conscious choice about whether the Answers are meaningful or not.</description>
        <documentation_url/>
        <finding_type>scan_finding</finding_type>
        <name>CodeSanity - Auto-generated Wizard Answers</name>
        <priority>1</priority>
        <resolution_details>Auto-generated Wizard Answer records should either be removed - in case they are not useful - or be kept. In the latter case, the order number must be set to a different value than 100 to indicate they should be kept - and no finding is created.</resolution_details>
        <run_condition/>
        <score_max>100</score_max>
        <score_min>0</score_min>
        <score_scale>1</score_scale>
        <script><![CDATA[(function (engine) {

	if (x_snc_codesanity.IsCheckApplicableToRecord())
	{
		if (current.order == 100)
		{
			engine.finding.increment();
		}
	}

})(engine);]]></script>
        <short_description>Auto-generated Wizard Answer Records should be removed or revised</short_description>
